  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum ($25,000) and has demonstrated remorse and accountability by initiating partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the sentence must be proportionate to the crime and the defendant's lack of a criminal history. The outburst from the spectator is disregarded as it is prejudicial and irrelevant to the legal sentencing guidelines. An incarceration period of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a punitive measure and a deterrent, while allowing for the continued repayment of the remaining stolen funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
